docs.abstract: The former vice president, trying to stem the damage from complaints about unwanted touching, said he realized “social norms have begun to change.”
docs.snippet: The former vice president, trying to stem the damage from complaints about unwanted touching, said he realized “social norms have begun to change.”
docs.lead_paragraph: For five days, Joseph R. Biden Jr. remained in the background as four women came forward saying they had been uncomfortable with the ways he had touched them. He put out three statements through a spokesman, but none of them was his own account or an acknowledgment of the discomfort he had caused.

headline.main: Joe Biden, in Video, Says He Will Be ‘More Mindful’ of Personal Space
headline.print_headline: ‘I Get It’: Biden Pledges Respect For Boundaries

docs.abstract: Here's why there are two races on the same day for the same House seat in Michigan.
docs.snippet: Here's why there are two races on the same day for the same House seat in Michigan.
docs.lead_paragraph: Back in December, Representative John Conyers Jr. resigned his seat in Michigan’s 13th District over sexual harassment allegations. He had been one of Congress’s longest-serving members, having represented the district, which is 57 percent black, for 52 years.

headline.main: Rashida Tlaib Won a Primary This Week. She Also Lost a Primary This Week.

docs.abstract: Talk of a recall campaign began almost as soon as Judge Persky handed down the sentence in 2016 to Brock Turner, a student at Stanford. It was criticized as being too lenient.
docs.snippet: Talk of a recall campaign began almost as soon as Judge Persky handed down the sentence in 2016 to Brock Turner, a student at Stanford. It was criticized as being too lenient.
docs.lead_paragraph: Aaron Persky, the California judge who drew national attention in 2016 when he sentenced a Stanford student to just six months in jail for sexually assaulting an unconscious woman, was recalled on Tuesday, according to The Associated Press. He is the first judge recalled in California in more than 80 years.

headline.main: California Voters Remove Judge Aaron Persky, Who Gave a 6-Month Sentence for Sexual Assault

docs.abstract: The abuse already common in many women’s everyday lives can be amplified in political campaigns, especially if the candidate is also a member of a minority group.
docs.snippet: The abuse already common in many women’s everyday lives can be amplified in political campaigns, especially if the candidate is also a member of a minority group.
docs.lead_paragraph: Four days before the 2016 congressional primary in her Northern California district, Erin Schrode woke up to tens of thousands of messages. They were everywhere: in her email, on her cellphone, on her Facebook and her Twitter and her Instagram.

docs.abstract: In an acerbic order, a federal judge said 32 counties with Puerto Rican populations were obligated to provide Spanish-language sample ballots.
docs.snippet: In an acerbic order, a federal judge said 32 counties with Puerto Rican populations were obligated to provide Spanish-language sample ballots.
docs.lead_paragraph: Florida officials must provide Spanish-language election materials in 32 counties with Puerto Rican populations, a federal judge ruled on Friday, granting part of what a Puerto Rican voter and several Latino advocacy groups had requested. But the judge concluded that there would not be enough time before the November elections to make other changes the plaintiffs had sought.

headline.main: Florida Must Provide Election Materials in Spanish, Judge Says
